WEBVTT

00:00.890 --> 00:04.162
<i>♪ I think that I like you,
ooh, ooh ♪</i>

00:04.250 --> 00:07.515
Meredith: <i>On average,
our hearts beat 70 times per minute.</i>

00:07.618 --> 00:10.303
<i>- ♪ Like you, like you ♪
- ♪ Ooh, ooh ♪</i>

00:10.602 --> 00:14.976
<i>- ♪ I think that I like you ♪
- ♪ Oooh, ooh ♪</i>

00:16.108 --> 00:18.334
<i>In the same 60-second period,</i>

00:18.422 --> 00:20.850
<i>we blink between
10 and 15 times,</i>

00:20.958 --> 00:22.303
<i>swallow once,</i>

00:22.536 --> 00:24.326
<i>and take up to 20 breaths.</i>

00:24.428 --> 00:26.982
[ Inhales sharply ] Okay,
you can't fall asleep here.

00:27.078 --> 00:28.334
The kids.

00:28.745 --> 00:30.084
You have to go,
please.

00:30.172 --> 00:31.537
Right.

00:31.982 --> 00:33.195
Go, go, go.
Come on.

00:33.283 --> 00:34.367
Okay.
Please.

00:34.455 --> 00:35.569
I'm up.
[ Sighs ]

00:35.672 --> 00:39.365
<i>♪ Shake that sugar,
show me what you're made of ♪</i>

00:39.456 --> 00:40.584
What are you
lookin' at?

00:40.672 --> 00:42.093
<i>- ♪ Make me want some more ♪
- [ Both chuckle ]</i>

00:42.185 --> 00:43.933
<i>♪ Oh, mi amore ♪</i>

00:44.021 --> 00:45.248
[ Chuckles ]

00:45.336 --> 00:47.631
- <i>♪ Dance with my flamingo ♪</i>
- [ Sighs ]

00:47.975 --> 00:49.779
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:50.102 --> 00:52.928
<i>♪ Give you all you want
and a little more ♪</i>

00:53.016 --> 00:54.179
Bye.

00:54.880 --> 00:57.018
Tip-toe.
Don't forget to tip-toe.

00:57.200 --> 00:58.373
Quiet as a mouse.

00:58.461 --> 00:59.834
<i>Our hearts beat...</i>

01:00.030 --> 01:01.100
[ Door closes ]

01:01.188 --> 01:02.975
<i>...our lungs breathe,</i>

01:03.063 --> 01:05.226
<i>our bodies keep us alive...</i>

01:05.474 --> 01:06.850
<i>♪ I think that I like you ♪</i>

01:06.938 --> 01:08.904
<i>...and most of us
barely notice.</i>

01:09.295 --> 01:10.529
♪ Ooh ♪

01:10.617 --> 01:14.029
Oh, hey... Zola.

01:14.117 --> 01:15.189
Uh...

01:15.277 --> 01:17.051
- <i>♪ I think that I like you ♪</i>
- [ Sighs ]

01:17.139 --> 01:18.482
<i>We just take it all
for granted.</i>

01:18.570 --> 01:19.590
Um...

01:19.678 --> 01:21.421
<i>♪ I think I like you a lot ♪</i>

01:21.800 --> 01:23.387
[ Insects chirping ]
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>

01:23.628 --> 01:25.403
[dog barking in distance ]
<font color=#00FF00>Season 15  Episode 22</font>

01:25.528 --> 01:27.528
Episode Title:
<font color=#FFFF00>"Head Over High Heels"</font>

01:27.615 --> 01:29.362
<font color=#ffff00>Sync corrections</font>  by  <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

01:29.495 --> 01:30.505
What did she say?

01:30.593 --> 01:31.888
Did she ask you what
you're doing here?

01:31.975 --> 01:33.145
- No.
- What is she doing up?

01:33.233 --> 01:34.816
I-I-I don't know.
She was thirsty, I guess.

01:34.903 --> 01:37.635
I mean, my kids know you
as the sad guy from the couch.

01:37.723 --> 01:39.899
An embarrassing chapter
in my life, yes.

01:39.987 --> 01:41.853
Have I apologized for that recently?
I'd like to. - [ Chuckles ]

01:41.947 --> 01:44.527
I mean, I had a whole plan
for telling my kids about us

01:44.654 --> 01:46.584
with ice cream, and they could
talk about their feelings,

01:46.671 --> 01:48.489
and now
it's just blown.

01:49.036 --> 01:50.057
[ Sighs ]

01:50.145 --> 01:51.200
What?
Why are you smiling?

01:51.288 --> 01:53.221
You were planning on
telling your kids about us?

01:53.885 --> 01:55.417
- [ Sighs ]
- Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

01:55.610 --> 01:57.250
- Um, what can I do?
- Don't be sorry.

01:57.338 --> 01:59.030
You can just go.
Quietly.

01:59.515 --> 02:00.661
Bye.

02:00.749 --> 02:01.775
Wait, wait, wait,
let me check,

02:01.862 --> 02:03.493
make sure
the coast is clear.

02:03.641 --> 02:09.122
[♪♪]

02:10.776 --> 02:12.622
[ Whispering ]
Okay, coast is clear.

02:13.678 --> 02:14.803
Okay.

02:14.958 --> 02:16.897
Bye.
Bye.

02:17.069 --> 02:23.514
[♪♪]

02:24.115 --> 02:26.388
[ Leo crying ] Yes, yes, yes,
Megan, I'm gonna be there.

02:26.491 --> 02:27.857
I said I'm gonna be there,
so...

02:27.945 --> 02:29.358
[ Sighs ] What do you mean
I might throw up?

02:29.445 --> 02:30.974
What kind of therapy
is this?

02:31.121 --> 02:33.138
[ Groans ] Okay, yes.
Yes, yes, yes.

02:33.226 --> 02:34.632
It's okay. It's okay.
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

02:34.719 --> 02:35.740
Listen, listen.

02:35.828 --> 02:36.833
Oh!
[ Phone clatters ]

02:36.921 --> 02:38.004
Lis...

02:38.115 --> 02:39.198
I'm gonna be there,
okay?

02:39.286 --> 02:40.989
Just...
I-I'll call you later.

02:41.077 --> 02:42.169
[ Crying continues ]

02:42.562 --> 02:44.263
[ Siren wailing in distance ]
No. No.

02:44.351 --> 02:46.966
I never told him
to call Ben "Dad."

02:47.927 --> 02:50.888
T... Y-Yes, I'm aware
that you are Tuck's father.

02:50.976 --> 02:53.059
And please do not raise
your voice at me...

02:53.166 --> 02:55.577
Hello? Tucker?

02:56.104 --> 02:57.379
M...

02:58.028 --> 02:59.059
[ Sighs ]

02:59.147 --> 03:03.263
My ex-husband overheard
our son call Ben "Dad."

03:03.350 --> 03:06.263
And now Tucker's hurt,
Tuck feels bad,

03:06.351 --> 03:07.826
- and Ben is oblivious...
- Thanks...

03:07.914 --> 03:09.841
And, somehow,
it's all my problem.

03:09.929 --> 03:12.224
Are you asking my opinion
about all of this?

03:12.326 --> 03:14.732
I would way rather give
my opinion about your life.

03:14.835 --> 03:15.909
Hmm.

03:15.997 --> 03:16.818
In that case,

03:16.906 --> 03:19.208
how did you tell Tuck when
you started dating Ben?

03:19.296 --> 03:20.839
Is this about
you and DeLuca?

03:21.184 --> 03:23.036
Oh, I see
everything, Grey.

03:23.124 --> 03:24.497
I am the chief.

03:24.732 --> 03:26.380
Uh-huh.
He told you.

03:26.468 --> 03:27.857
Who? Richard?

03:27.945 --> 03:29.324
[ Chuckling ] Well,
the man's very chatty.

03:29.411 --> 03:30.825
[ Chuckles ]

03:30.913 --> 03:33.716
So, Zola actually saw him
last night at the house

03:33.812 --> 03:36.107
before I had a chance
to talk to her, so it was...

03:36.256 --> 03:37.442
- She's back.
- Oh.

03:37.530 --> 03:39.200
- What?
- Jo's back. She's here.

03:39.288 --> 03:41.380
Oh, and here, I thought
she might be dead, or...

03:41.468 --> 03:42.785
Don't do that.
Don't give a speech about

03:42.872 --> 03:43.779
how you thought
she was dead

03:43.867 --> 03:45.866
or lost a limb or left me
or whatever, all right?

03:45.954 --> 03:47.427
She's not okay,
and I don't know why.

03:47.515 --> 03:49.450
Just don't be Bailey
about it, please.

03:49.863 --> 03:51.146
Meredith:
[ Gasps ]

03:51.570 --> 03:53.943
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

03:54.108 --> 03:55.483
Dr. Karev.

03:57.520 --> 03:58.893
Welcome back.

03:58.981 --> 04:00.036
[ Sighs ]

04:00.179 --> 04:01.682
I'll be in the lab.

04:02.857 --> 04:06.185
[♪♪]

04:07.516 --> 04:10.405
That was way worse than if
you had been Bailey about it.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.866
- Mnh.
- Mm-hmm.

04:13.742 --> 04:15.402
Woman on P.A.:
<i>Dr. Bashine to the OR.</i>

04:15.490 --> 04:17.671
- <i>Dr. Linda Bashine to the OR.</i>
- Is it ready?

04:17.759 --> 04:18.882
It's ready.

04:19.084 --> 04:20.112
So, it's happening?

04:20.200 --> 04:21.113
It's happening.

04:21.201 --> 04:22.148
Can we tell them?

04:22.266 --> 04:24.350
W-We can tell them, but try to
contain your wagging tail

04:24.437 --> 04:26.078
because this could be nothing
and could do nothing.

04:26.165 --> 04:28.195
We don't want to bait them
with false hope. It's cruel.

04:28.282 --> 04:29.889
Right.
Just hang on.

04:29.977 --> 04:31.083
What?

04:31.171 --> 04:33.139
I need to wag my tail
for a second out here.

04:33.691 --> 04:35.531
[ Exhales sharply ]
Man, I hope this is not nothing.

04:35.618 --> 04:36.686
[ Chuckles ]

04:36.774 --> 04:38.092
Me, too.
[ Sighs ]

04:39.725 --> 04:42.333
So, wait, you're saying my mom
might be able to use her arms again?

04:42.420 --> 04:43.687
We're saying
there's a clinical trial

04:43.774 --> 04:46.226
with stem cells being directly
injected into the cervical spine.

04:46.313 --> 04:48.054
That's turning quadriplegics
into paraplegics.

04:48.141 --> 04:49.384
That's...
That's what you said.

04:49.472 --> 04:51.085
In some cases, yes.

04:51.370 --> 04:52.678
We just need
your approval,

04:52.766 --> 04:55.140
and then we can get started as
soon as the stem cells arrive.

04:55.227 --> 04:56.647
Mom?

04:57.545 --> 04:59.491
Yes.
Yes, please.

04:59.663 --> 05:02.624
[♪♪]

05:02.893 --> 05:04.248
Are you nervous?

05:04.336 --> 05:06.225
I throw up before
every job interview.

05:06.357 --> 05:07.459
I just ace them.

05:07.547 --> 05:10.170
So arrogant.
I love it.

05:10.258 --> 05:11.835
But why
San Francisco?

05:12.053 --> 05:14.077
My fellowship year
is almost up.

05:14.165 --> 05:15.707
I have to interview at places before I...
No, I'm saying there's

05:15.794 --> 05:17.827
a lot of
excellent jobs right here.

05:18.045 --> 05:19.788
And I hear
the weather is worse

05:19.876 --> 05:21.460
in San Francisco than
it is in Seattle,

05:21.548 --> 05:22.613
and the rent
is triple.

05:22.701 --> 05:25.288
And... hills.

05:27.933 --> 05:30.100
You're on my vertebroplasty
today, right?

05:31.928 --> 05:33.193
I'll see you there.

05:33.280 --> 05:34.319
[♪♪]

05:34.407 --> 05:36.038
And the sports teams!

05:36.126 --> 05:37.981
Seattle has
better sports teams!

05:38.069 --> 05:39.764
- I'm guessing.
- [ Groans ]

05:40.032 --> 05:41.235
It's a bowel obstruction.

05:41.323 --> 05:42.874
I know the symptoms.
I have IBD.

05:42.962 --> 05:44.584
I've had three obstructions
and three surgeries.

05:44.671 --> 05:46.087
All right,
what are your symptoms?

05:46.175 --> 05:48.717
Pain, bloating, cramping...
Bowel obstruction symptoms.

05:48.805 --> 05:50.090
- Ow!
- Okay,

05:50.178 --> 05:51.468
I'd love to take
your word for it,

05:51.555 --> 05:53.858
- but I have to get you a...
- Get a CT. Yeah, I know.

05:53.946 --> 05:55.131
Can you just
order it, please?

05:55.219 --> 05:56.280
It really hurts.

05:56.368 --> 05:57.835
Okay.

05:58.514 --> 05:59.733
Dr. DeLuca?

05:59.833 --> 06:00.856
DeLuca: Yeah?

06:00.991 --> 06:04.030
[♪♪]

06:04.125 --> 06:06.733
Uh, I have a patient
who's... [ Gasps ]

06:06.821 --> 06:08.999
- Are you a doctor?
- Uh, I am, yes,

06:09.087 --> 06:10.679
but I'm gonna need you to
check in with her first, okay?

06:10.766 --> 06:15.202
I-I just had a little trouble
puttin' on my shoes.

06:15.382 --> 06:17.585
- Oh. Oh.
- [ Gasps ] Oh.

06:19.026 --> 06:21.098
Yeah, maybe you should
help her first.

06:21.186 --> 06:23.186
[♪♪]

06:29.177 --> 06:31.272
I see a small
pericardial effusion.

06:31.430 --> 06:32.889
Gemma:
The shoes were new.

06:32.977 --> 06:34.310
I went dancing.

06:34.404 --> 06:38.303
A little underground club
I was supposedly too old for.

06:38.662 --> 06:41.085
Had a few shots
too many.

06:41.785 --> 06:45.194
And I took off my shoes to walk
up the stairs to my apartment,

06:45.282 --> 06:47.655
and... that's all
I remember.

06:47.743 --> 06:49.131
Maggie:
You slept like this?

06:49.219 --> 06:50.523
Oh, crap.

06:50.610 --> 06:51.741
Gemma?

06:51.829 --> 06:54.014
Richard: Uh, excuse me.
You two know each other?

06:54.217 --> 06:55.663
Um...

06:56.490 --> 06:59.113
Through, um,
a mutual friend.

06:59.544 --> 07:01.483
Well, Ollie isn't
around anymore,

07:01.571 --> 07:03.444
so thank you
for your concern,

07:03.532 --> 07:06.275
but, as you can see,
I'm... I'm all set here.

07:06.551 --> 07:07.928
Gemma,
how did this happen?

07:08.016 --> 07:10.545
I think you and I both know
how this happened.

07:10.809 --> 07:15.217
[♪♪]

07:15.589 --> 07:19.053
Josh Sterman, 21,
has hereditary osteoporosis

07:19.141 --> 07:20.692
that caused
a compression fracture

07:20.780 --> 07:22.350
at T-11 to T-12,

07:22.438 --> 07:24.761
scheduled for
a percutaneous vertebroplasty.

07:24.849 --> 07:27.756
I'll inject cement right here
into the vertebral body

07:27.844 --> 07:28.975
to restore
its integrity,

07:29.063 --> 07:30.264
then you'll be
good to go.

07:30.378 --> 07:31.457
You'll be out of here
in time for dinner.

07:31.544 --> 07:32.747
Pop-Pop?

07:32.990 --> 07:34.628
Dr. Bailey!

07:34.780 --> 07:36.574
[ Both chuckle ]

07:36.833 --> 07:38.394
Josh, you remember
Dr. Bailey?

07:38.482 --> 07:40.872
She's the one who takes out part
of my bowel every few years.

07:40.959 --> 07:41.873
[ Chuckles ]

07:41.961 --> 07:43.949
Uh,
recurrent diverticulitis.

07:44.110 --> 07:45.550
Now, the last time
I saw you,

07:45.638 --> 07:48.488
you were, what, a foot shorter
and studying for the SATs.

07:48.576 --> 07:49.659
He aced 'em!

07:49.747 --> 07:50.792
Aww.
And thanks to you,

07:50.880 --> 07:53.464
I saw him graduate from
high school and get into Udub.

07:53.552 --> 07:55.019
Next stop,
business school.

07:55.107 --> 07:56.910
I can't finish
those applications

07:57.021 --> 07:58.402
until my back
stops hurting.

07:58.490 --> 07:59.511
He's getting

07:59.599 --> 08:01.431
- a vertebroplasty today.
- Oh.

08:01.519 --> 08:03.363
- Did I say that right?
- [ Chuckles ]

08:03.451 --> 08:05.597
I thought we'd be seeing
Dr. Lincoln,

08:05.685 --> 08:06.910
the fancy sports guy?

08:06.998 --> 08:09.699
Oh, well, Dr. Kim is
Dr. Lincoln's fellow.

08:09.795 --> 08:12.613
He's being wooed
by the top hospitals

08:12.701 --> 08:14.300
and some
pro-sports teams.

08:14.388 --> 08:16.182
You're lucky you've got him
while he's still here.

08:16.269 --> 08:17.472
Thank you,
Chief Bailey.

08:17.560 --> 08:20.050
So, I will, uh, check back
a little later.

08:20.160 --> 08:21.283
[ Chuckles ]

08:21.394 --> 08:22.949
Pressure's on, man.

08:24.362 --> 08:25.839
[ Monitor beeping ]

08:26.530 --> 08:27.894
Wow.

08:29.610 --> 08:31.074
Which one
is that one?

08:32.855 --> 08:34.518
The Arc de Triomphe.

08:34.606 --> 08:36.128
From Paris?

08:36.605 --> 08:40.027
The golden plate represents
the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

08:40.115 --> 08:42.113
Hm.
It's cool.

08:44.135 --> 08:45.503
Be back in a second.

08:46.589 --> 08:48.233
Woman on P.A.: <i>Dr. Ruta,
please contact the lab.</i>

08:48.320 --> 08:49.800
<i>Dr. Ruta,
please contact the lab.</i>

08:49.888 --> 08:52.011
Any word from
the rare blood organizations?

08:52.099 --> 08:53.683
Well, I'm waiting on
that call from Amsterdam.

08:53.770 --> 08:55.636
He's getting weaker.
I need that blood.

08:55.724 --> 08:58.035
I've called Cristina.
I even called Marie Cerone.

08:58.123 --> 08:59.136
Thanks.

08:59.232 --> 09:00.966
[ Sighs ]

09:01.474 --> 09:02.753
What about Jo?

09:03.145 --> 09:04.581
She said anything yet?

09:05.130 --> 09:06.443
Not at all?

09:06.590 --> 09:08.283
It's happening again.
[ Sighs ]

09:08.370 --> 09:09.751
It's not. No, they're
happy for a while...

09:09.838 --> 09:11.480
- It's not happening.
- ...then they break...

09:11.567 --> 09:13.695
- She's not broken.
- ...and then they leave me.

09:13.783 --> 09:14.866
Listen to me.

09:14.954 --> 09:16.077
You have to trust her.

09:16.165 --> 09:17.328
She isn't Izzie.

09:17.416 --> 09:18.742
She isn't Ava or Lexie.

09:18.830 --> 09:20.187
She isn't your mother.

09:20.275 --> 09:22.461
And she's not broken,
and neither are you.

09:22.549 --> 09:24.351
She's going
through something.

09:24.710 --> 09:27.503
And she's been through worse and
come out on the other side fine.

09:27.591 --> 09:29.547
She's just not ready
to talk about it yet.

09:29.703 --> 09:30.765
I've been there.

09:30.853 --> 09:33.461
You give me space.
You give me time.

09:33.820 --> 09:35.054
Right?

09:35.142 --> 09:36.305
Okay.

09:36.393 --> 09:38.273
It's not
happening again.

09:39.801 --> 09:42.044
[♪♪]

09:42.388 --> 09:43.389
[ Sighs ]

09:43.670 --> 09:49.222
[♪♪]

09:49.826 --> 09:51.115
[ Knock on door ]

09:51.810 --> 09:53.233
Wow.

09:54.158 --> 09:55.811
That's a lot
of journals.

09:55.903 --> 09:57.889
Oh, you got binders, too.
Great.

09:58.050 --> 10:01.311
Yeah, this is the lab where boring
things go to get more boring.

10:01.399 --> 10:02.717
Bailey's really
piling it on

10:02.805 --> 10:04.217
now that she's
chief again, huh?

10:04.305 --> 10:06.318
Yeah, didn't help that
I was out for a while.

10:07.368 --> 10:08.654
Mm-hmm.

10:08.808 --> 10:10.826
Okay, well, I don't want to
bother you, then.

10:11.175 --> 10:12.506
Bother me how?

10:12.607 --> 10:13.647
Oh, nothing.

10:13.735 --> 10:14.937
I just thought
maybe you could help me

10:15.024 --> 10:16.262
with my
spray-on skin research,

10:16.350 --> 10:19.006
but you seem pretty
underwater, so...

10:19.419 --> 10:20.490
Wait.

10:20.578 --> 10:23.321
That sounds way better
than any of this.

10:23.442 --> 10:25.146
Then again,
so does a root canal.

10:25.234 --> 10:27.943
Well, that's just the winning
attitude I'm looking for.

10:28.109 --> 10:29.612
[ Car horns honking ]

10:29.808 --> 10:32.181
- So, you're a licensed therapist?
- I am.

10:32.487 --> 10:34.600
'Cause I don't believe in,
you know...

10:34.718 --> 10:37.154
alternative...
whatever...

10:37.242 --> 10:40.615
You know, holistic...
voodoo stuff.

10:40.703 --> 10:42.656
No voodoo.
Got it.

10:43.396 --> 10:44.654
[ Inhales sharply ]

10:44.742 --> 10:46.865
Well, Megan
swears by this...

10:46.953 --> 10:48.765
Whatever this thing is
that you're doing, so...

10:48.852 --> 10:50.232
Neuro Emotional
Technique.

10:50.320 --> 10:51.201
Mm.

10:51.289 --> 10:53.193
It's a psycho-therapeutic
modality

10:53.281 --> 10:54.576
in which I use
muscle testing

10:54.664 --> 10:56.082
to determine
where in your body

10:56.170 --> 10:58.642
you might be holding on to
unresolved patterns of stress,

10:58.946 --> 11:00.950
- like trauma, physical injury...
- Hmm. Muscle testing.

11:01.037 --> 11:04.053
Is that like when you, uh,
get weak when you're lying?

11:04.141 --> 11:06.192
Because that... that is
a party trick, not science.

11:06.280 --> 11:07.318
[ Chuckles ]
You're right.

11:07.406 --> 11:09.818
It's not the most precise
system of diagnosis,

11:09.906 --> 11:12.529
but, often, when your mind is
trying to hide something from you,

11:12.669 --> 11:14.756
your body will still
throw you under the bus.

11:15.240 --> 11:17.670
Well...
[clears throat]

11:17.758 --> 11:20.100
This helped Megan
with her trauma, so...

11:20.833 --> 11:22.982
And she was held hostage
in Iraq.

11:23.070 --> 11:25.193
For a decade.
Presumed dead.

11:25.327 --> 11:29.053
So I figured, if it helped her,
then what the hell?

11:29.825 --> 11:31.170
[ Smacks lips ]

11:33.019 --> 11:34.919
Megan is convinced
that I am incapable

11:35.007 --> 11:36.652
of allowing joy to
exist in my life

11:36.740 --> 11:37.904
due to some
unprocessed trauma

11:37.969 --> 11:41.858
that your weird voodoo therapy is
supposed to help me with, so...

11:42.756 --> 11:44.397
Do you think
she's right?

11:46.989 --> 11:48.428
Ow!

11:48.755 --> 11:50.568
This is worse
than it's ever been.

11:50.656 --> 11:52.123
I-I know it's hard,
Avi,

11:52.211 --> 11:54.224
but I'm gonna need you to hold
still for another little while.

11:54.311 --> 11:55.279
Okay?
You're doing great.

11:55.367 --> 11:56.373
[ Telephone rings ]

11:56.592 --> 11:58.347
- Hey, you paged?
- Hey.

11:58.435 --> 12:01.256
Uh, yes, I have a 24-year-old
patient with IBD. [ Groaning ]

12:01.344 --> 12:03.381
She presents with
severe abdominal pain.

12:03.475 --> 12:05.123
She thinks
it's an obstruction,

12:05.211 --> 12:06.679
but, I mean, she's in
way too much pain.

12:06.766 --> 12:07.804
I-I think it
might be a perf.

12:07.891 --> 12:08.895
- Ow.
- Yeah.

12:08.983 --> 12:09.807
- Okay.
- I'm... I'm waiting for

12:09.895 --> 12:11.178
the images to come up, so...

12:11.266 --> 12:12.180
Okay.

12:12.268 --> 12:14.068
How was, uh,
Zola this morning?

12:14.156 --> 12:15.668
- She freaked out?
- I...

12:15.756 --> 12:17.146
- Traumatized? [ Chuckling ]
- I mean,

12:17.233 --> 12:18.772
I don't think so,
actually.

12:18.860 --> 12:21.139
I think she was
kind of normal-ish.

12:21.740 --> 12:23.685
I mean, it's hard to hear her
over my own tell-tale heart.

12:23.772 --> 12:25.066
Right?
I mean, why...

12:25.154 --> 12:26.037
Why do we feel so guilty?

12:26.125 --> 12:27.709
We're not doing
anything wrong, right?

12:27.797 --> 12:29.178
Well...

12:30.060 --> 12:31.269
Do you even like kids?

12:31.357 --> 12:32.350
What?

12:32.438 --> 12:33.932
Well, we really haven't
talked about it,

12:34.019 --> 12:35.615
and I do
have three of them.

12:36.432 --> 12:39.897
I have 16 first cousins,
age 2 to 15.

12:40.006 --> 12:43.147
The 14-year-old, Tony,
always calls me about girls.

12:43.235 --> 12:44.903
He's been doing that since he was 9.
[ Chuckles ]

12:44.990 --> 12:46.662
The 5-year-old, Sonia,

12:46.750 --> 12:48.725
she attaches herself to my leg
when she sees me,

12:48.813 --> 12:51.106
and I basically wear her
like a leg brace. [ Laughs ]

12:51.238 --> 12:53.256
The 2-year-old,
Nicholas,

12:53.344 --> 12:55.091
likes to put things in my hair
and then dig them out.

12:55.178 --> 12:56.514
[ Laughs ]

12:57.699 --> 13:00.115
Your problem's not gonna be
that I don't like kids, Mer.

13:00.203 --> 13:02.710
Your problem's gonna be that your
kids might like me more than you.

13:02.797 --> 13:03.865
- You think?
- Mm-hmm.

13:03.953 --> 13:04.813
Oh.
[ Machine beeps ]

13:04.901 --> 13:05.983
Scans are up.

13:06.359 --> 13:07.848
Okay, Avi,
your scans are up.

13:07.936 --> 13:08.926
We're almost done here.

13:09.014 --> 13:10.647
Oh, my God.

13:10.735 --> 13:12.209
You didn't run
a pregnancy test?!

13:12.297 --> 13:14.980
No, no, no, Qadri said she ran
standard labs and then a CT.

13:15.068 --> 13:15.943
What... Oh, my God.

13:16.030 --> 13:17.006
You guys,
I'm not pregnant.

13:17.094 --> 13:19.287
I just have...
Oww!

13:19.405 --> 13:22.528
Avi, you are pregnant,
and you are in labor,

13:22.616 --> 13:24.272
and it looks like
you're crowning.

13:24.360 --> 13:26.186
What?
What?

13:26.274 --> 13:28.597
- Let's page OB and page the chief.
- Yep.

13:28.780 --> 13:30.678
- [ Avi breathing heavily ]
- [ Dialing ]

13:34.647 --> 13:37.647
Uh, Dr. Pierce,
can you excuse us?

13:37.785 --> 13:39.981
I-I'd like a few minutes alone
with Gemma if there's time.

13:40.068 --> 13:40.881
- Of course.
- No.

13:40.969 --> 13:42.811
Gemma. No, I don't
want him in here.

13:42.899 --> 13:43.686
[ Sighs ]
Dr. Webber...

13:43.774 --> 13:44.936
Gemma,
don't be ridiculous.

13:45.024 --> 13:47.187
- You are not my doctor.
- No, I'm your friend.

13:47.275 --> 13:49.154
And I owe it to Ollie
to check on you.

13:49.242 --> 13:50.865
Ollie is dead.

13:50.953 --> 13:53.866
I don't want you in here
preaching at me, praying at me,

13:53.954 --> 13:56.349
- pretending you relate.
- Except I do.

13:56.437 --> 13:58.358
No, you don't.
You got a wife.

13:59.187 --> 14:00.326
You got kids.

14:00.414 --> 14:02.662
I had a sponsor.
I had Ollie.

14:02.750 --> 14:05.115
And now I got a stiletto
in my chest

14:05.309 --> 14:07.779
and a bottle of tequila
waiting for me when I get home.

14:07.867 --> 14:11.131
And I don't want to hear what
you got to think about any of it.

14:11.247 --> 14:13.459
So get out of my room
before I call security.

14:13.547 --> 14:14.910
Oh,
for God's sakes, Gemma.

14:14.998 --> 14:16.365
Get out.

14:17.320 --> 14:20.076
Um, you better run
a tox screen,

14:20.164 --> 14:21.319
make sure
she's not still drunk.

14:21.406 --> 14:23.233
You arrogant
son of a bitch!

14:23.321 --> 14:25.131
Get out!
Get out!

14:25.219 --> 14:27.193
- Gemma, please calm down.
- Get out!

14:27.281 --> 14:28.312
- Get out!
- Please... Gemma, please hold still.

14:28.399 --> 14:30.285
- Get out!
- Dr, Webber, get out! Please.

14:30.373 --> 14:32.256
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:33.681 --> 14:34.644
[ Avi groaning ]

14:34.732 --> 14:36.303
- Did you page OB?
- DeLuca: Yeah,

14:36.391 --> 14:37.640
it's a busy
delivery day, apparently.

14:37.727 --> 14:39.772
Oww!

14:39.860 --> 14:41.100
Okay, Avi,
good, push!

14:41.188 --> 14:43.170
How do you give
a pregnant woman a CT?

14:43.271 --> 14:44.701
Qadri ordered the CT.

14:44.789 --> 14:46.365
'Cause I had
my period yesterday.

14:46.453 --> 14:48.306
This makes no seeeense!

14:48.394 --> 14:50.147
Bear down, Avi.
Good job.

14:50.235 --> 14:51.037
Oh!

14:51.125 --> 14:52.193
Oh, my God.

14:52.537 --> 14:53.544
Two wombs!

14:53.633 --> 14:55.086
- What? Ah!
- Hm.

14:55.174 --> 14:56.088
Oh, look at this!

14:56.176 --> 14:58.467
It's a u-uterus didelphys!

14:58.571 --> 14:59.734
Look at this, Grey!

14:59.822 --> 15:01.615
I'm a little busy right now,
Dr. Bailey!

15:01.703 --> 15:03.381
What the hell
is uter... Aaah!

15:03.473 --> 15:06.506
You have two uteri, but you're
only pregnant in one!

15:06.609 --> 15:08.458
Oh, my Go-o-o-o-d!

15:08.546 --> 15:10.829
- Good job, good job, Avi.
- [ Screaming ]

15:10.917 --> 15:12.248
You're almost there.

15:12.336 --> 15:13.616
DeLuca: Head down, okay?
Come on.

15:14.497 --> 15:16.272
[ Infant crying ]
Okay.

15:16.889 --> 15:18.717
Okay.

15:19.037 --> 15:21.912
Here's your baby boy.

15:22.727 --> 15:26.430
[ Breathing heavily ]

15:26.517 --> 15:32.678
[♪♪]

15:34.212 --> 15:35.425
[ Sighs ]

15:35.513 --> 15:37.796
So, did you ever follow through
with the whole...

15:38.202 --> 15:39.499
birth-mom thing?

15:39.587 --> 15:40.569
Have you been talking
to Alex?

15:40.657 --> 15:42.335
Not about that, no.

15:42.678 --> 15:46.154
- Well, you were right.
- About?

15:46.242 --> 15:47.154
You know what?

15:47.256 --> 15:48.380
Y-You said that you
needed me to help you

15:48.467 --> 15:49.381
with spray-on skin,

15:49.469 --> 15:50.749
so can we just
get to it already?

15:50.836 --> 15:51.654
It's a process.

15:51.742 --> 15:54.615
Right now, we're focused on
aerosolization and coverage.

15:55.372 --> 15:56.544
I was wrong.

15:56.632 --> 15:57.560
This is a lab

15:57.648 --> 15:59.811
where boring things go
to get more boring.

16:00.065 --> 16:01.065
Mm.

16:01.439 --> 16:03.216
Injecting cement.

16:03.853 --> 16:06.029
<i>♪ Your grace ♪</i>

16:06.117 --> 16:08.162
<i>♪ Your grace ♪</i>

16:08.368 --> 16:09.748
<i>♪ Your grace ♪</i>

16:09.848 --> 16:10.981
Is that it?

16:11.069 --> 16:13.732
Just because I made it look easy
doesn't mean it was.

16:14.107 --> 16:18.013
[♪♪]

16:19.085 --> 16:20.435
Do you have them?

16:20.602 --> 16:22.271
The... The stem cells?
Are they here?

16:22.359 --> 16:23.396
Uh, not yet.

16:23.484 --> 16:25.592
Now we just have to get some
blood samples from your mom

16:25.679 --> 16:26.959
before the procedure.

16:27.047 --> 16:28.646
I can't quite breathe.

16:28.941 --> 16:31.716
I-I mean, I can't
get a deep breath.

16:33.060 --> 16:35.482
And I think it's
because I'm so aware.

16:36.148 --> 16:38.311
I'm aware of my hands.

16:38.438 --> 16:40.351
I'm aware of my legs.

16:40.509 --> 16:42.279
My fingers.

16:42.889 --> 16:46.672
When I walk... every step...
I'm aware.

16:46.783 --> 16:48.076
I'm in awe.

16:48.404 --> 16:49.779
We're anxious
and we're depressed

16:49.867 --> 16:53.009
and we mope and we worry
about an extra five pounds

16:53.097 --> 16:54.959
or our...
Our stupid job.

16:55.071 --> 16:56.575
Since the accident,
all I can think about

16:56.662 --> 17:00.775
are my feet
and my hands

17:02.231 --> 17:04.173
and how grateful
I am for them.

17:04.261 --> 17:05.983
♪ Way too close
to color your comfort ♪

17:06.071 --> 17:09.429
- <i>♪ All dressed up but kept undercover ♪</i>
- And I want them for my mom.

17:09.539 --> 17:12.037
[ Voice breaking ]
I want her hands back.

17:12.919 --> 17:16.490
I want them so badly,
I can't... quite breathe.

17:16.578 --> 17:19.334
<i>♪ All dressed up
but kept undercover ♪</i>

17:19.624 --> 17:21.538
All right, we need to suspend
the patient's breathing

17:21.625 --> 17:23.623
for about two minutes
while we inject.

17:23.788 --> 17:26.611
Lucky for everybody, I can do
a lot in, uh, two minutes.

17:28.348 --> 17:29.389
Y...
What?

17:29.477 --> 17:30.810
Oh.

17:30.928 --> 17:32.787
You miss
your boyfriend.

17:33.006 --> 17:34.037
Who?

17:34.125 --> 17:35.404
Ortho Barbie.
[ Chuckles ]

17:35.492 --> 17:38.638
Shepherd, I can't believe
you have a thing with a jock!

17:38.726 --> 17:40.545
It's not... Shut up.

17:40.633 --> 17:42.626
Is it weird having sex
with a cartoon character?

17:42.714 --> 17:44.607
Does he drip ink on you
when he sweats?

17:44.695 --> 17:47.404
[ Chuckles ] Okay, I made you laugh.
Come on. Spill.

17:47.492 --> 17:49.631
I need deets, and you,
obviously... you need advice.

17:49.719 --> 17:50.912
Fine.

17:51.000 --> 17:53.082
Yes, he looks
like a cartoon God,

17:53.170 --> 17:54.982
and the sex
is athletic,

17:55.070 --> 17:58.290
and there is eye contact,
and nobody cries after,

17:58.378 --> 18:00.531
and he's funny and fun
and easy to hang out with,

18:00.619 --> 18:01.631
which is just
confusing to me

18:01.718 --> 18:02.887
because it's
[Laughing] so not my type.

18:02.974 --> 18:04.513
Oh!
Okay.

18:04.709 --> 18:06.067
He's your Altman.
Hm.

18:06.155 --> 18:07.318
- My Altman?
- Yeah,

18:07.406 --> 18:10.318
you know, somebody so good
and unbroken and kind

18:10.406 --> 18:11.608
that they just seem
wrong for you,

18:11.695 --> 18:12.658
but, really, I mean,
you... [Chuckles]

18:12.746 --> 18:14.029
You've never
been happier.

18:14.117 --> 18:16.115
So, yeah,
he's your Altman.

18:16.203 --> 18:17.576
Oh, Tom.

18:17.692 --> 18:18.982
You poor guy.

18:20.774 --> 18:23.865
So, you came home from Germany,
and you got back with Amelia.

18:24.154 --> 18:25.615
But that
wasn't what you wanted.

18:25.703 --> 18:26.748
Owen: It was.

18:26.836 --> 18:29.170
Amelia was... perfect.

18:29.420 --> 18:32.253
I mean, if there was...
There was no Teddy, then...

18:32.341 --> 18:33.881
- There is a Teddy.
- No, there's not.

18:33.969 --> 18:35.607
I mean, she and I,
we just...

18:35.760 --> 18:37.029
[Chuckles]
we have bad timing.

18:37.117 --> 18:38.570
But the timing was right
in Germany,

18:38.658 --> 18:40.162
and still, you blew it up.
Accidentally.

18:40.249 --> 18:41.623
Was it an accident?

18:42.212 --> 18:45.125
It's the opposite of what you
went to Germany to do, Owen.

18:45.406 --> 18:46.659
So why would you
blow it?

18:46.747 --> 18:49.357
You're not stupid.
You don't like hurting people.

18:50.036 --> 18:51.506
Why would you do it?

18:52.021 --> 18:54.896
Uh, I...

18:56.674 --> 18:57.755
I don't know.

18:57.843 --> 18:59.733
Well, it seems like you
might be caught in a pattern.

18:59.820 --> 19:00.646
And if we can find

19:00.734 --> 19:02.249
the original event
that started that pattern,

19:02.336 --> 19:04.410
we can just stop it
from replaying.

19:04.498 --> 19:05.553
That's it.

19:05.641 --> 19:07.384
And that's your
E.N.T. thing?

19:07.472 --> 19:09.725
It's N.E.T., but whatever.
[ Breathes sharply ]

19:09.848 --> 19:10.841
Are you up for that?

19:10.929 --> 19:12.279
[ Clears throat ]

19:13.522 --> 19:16.019
Does it involve electric shocks
of any kind?

19:16.107 --> 19:17.295
[ Both chuckle ]

19:17.383 --> 19:18.803
I'm on my way
to a consult,

19:18.891 --> 19:20.365
but I wanted to make sure
everything went okay.

19:20.452 --> 19:22.529
Josh was awesome.
Access site looks great.

19:22.617 --> 19:23.513
How do you feel?

19:23.601 --> 19:25.634
No more stabbing knives in my back.
[ Laughter ]

19:25.722 --> 19:27.069
I think we're better
than okay, Chief.

19:27.156 --> 19:27.844
- Good.
- Hey,

19:27.932 --> 19:29.764
what's the over/under
on the bathroom situation?

19:29.851 --> 19:31.139
- Ooh, ooh.
- Do I need to continue to lie here?

19:31.226 --> 19:32.888
- You can go.
- I'll stop by later.

19:33.554 --> 19:35.144
All right, coming down.

19:35.232 --> 19:37.912
- Ooh.
- Nico: Good, careful, careful.

19:38.023 --> 19:39.106
Any tightness?

19:39.194 --> 19:40.717
No, no, I'm good.

19:41.236 --> 19:42.982
Ah, so,
what's your number one?

19:43.070 --> 19:44.889
UCSF, apparently.

19:44.977 --> 19:45.943
[ Chuckles lightly ]

19:46.031 --> 19:47.637
Well, I have a Skype interview
with them later, actually.

19:47.724 --> 19:49.397
Blow it off, man.
Hospitals are boring.

19:49.485 --> 19:50.960
Find yourself a hockey team,
you know?

19:51.047 --> 19:52.953
Fights, skates to the face,
busted shoulders.

19:53.041 --> 19:54.544
It's a real money-maker
right there.

19:54.632 --> 19:55.795
[ Gasps, groans ]

19:55.883 --> 19:57.911
Josh? Josh?
Josh?

19:57.999 --> 19:58.817
- Call a code!
- Oh, my God.

19:58.905 --> 19:59.920
- We need a gurney over here.
- Oh, my God.

20:00.007 --> 20:00.708
- [ Alarm beeping ]
- Josh.

20:00.796 --> 20:01.810
- What's... What's happening?
- We need help.

20:01.897 --> 20:02.880
Take him outside.
Get a crash cart now.

20:02.968 --> 20:04.084
What's happening?
Oh, my God, Josh!

20:04.171 --> 20:05.454
- Get me cardio.
- Josh!

20:05.616 --> 20:07.137
Start bagging him
and get an ABG now!

20:12.977 --> 20:15.825
[ Monitor beeping ]

20:16.197 --> 20:17.473
How's she doing?

20:17.561 --> 20:19.809
I just need to make sure
that her heart isn't affected,

20:19.897 --> 20:21.373
and then I'll do
a pericardial window.

20:21.460 --> 20:22.920
It's pretty simple.

20:23.951 --> 20:25.801
You really shouldn't
be here, Richard.

20:27.460 --> 20:29.145
The last time
I saw Gemma,

20:29.233 --> 20:32.348
she was taking a cake
for 17 years' sobriety.

20:33.559 --> 20:35.145
Then Ollie died,

20:35.491 --> 20:37.708
and I stopped going to
meetings for a while,

20:37.796 --> 20:39.700
and I guess
Gemma did, too.

20:40.771 --> 20:42.489
But you didn't drink.

20:43.482 --> 20:44.935
No, no.

20:45.023 --> 20:47.856
I took a baseball bat
to a bar.

20:48.045 --> 20:50.630
And if I didn't have a lot of
money to settle with the bar,

20:50.718 --> 20:51.880
I would've
lost my license.

20:51.968 --> 20:54.067
I could've
gone to prison.

20:54.187 --> 20:55.980
I was a dry drunk,
Maggie,

20:56.388 --> 20:58.840
and I was angry,
and it was painful,

20:58.928 --> 21:00.301
and...

21:01.211 --> 21:03.004
if it weren't
for Catherine, I...

21:03.607 --> 21:04.930
[ Door opens ]

21:05.106 --> 21:07.192
Dr. Pierce, we have a 911 page
for cardio from ortho.

21:07.280 --> 21:08.741
Altman's in surgery,
and so is Roberts.

21:08.828 --> 21:10.286
Oh, go, go.
I can handle it.

21:10.477 --> 21:11.496
She doesn't want you
on her case.

21:11.583 --> 21:13.236
Look, I'll talk Qadri
through it.

21:13.494 --> 21:15.537
- Go where you're needed, Maggie.
- Okay.

21:15.625 --> 21:19.324
[♪♪]

21:19.412 --> 21:20.525
DeLuca:
Hi, Avi.

21:20.635 --> 21:21.645
How you feeling?

21:21.733 --> 21:22.996
[ Baby coos ]
Hey.

21:23.084 --> 21:24.417
- Avi: Look at him.
- Hello.

21:24.505 --> 21:25.668
Look at what I made.

21:25.756 --> 21:26.999
[ Gasps ]
Yeah.

21:27.257 --> 21:28.590
[ Cellphone ringing ]

21:29.254 --> 21:30.480
[ Groans ]
It's Tucker.

21:30.664 --> 21:31.879
Again.

21:31.968 --> 21:33.631
I mean, really.

21:33.719 --> 21:37.043
There are worse things
than to have two good men

21:37.131 --> 21:38.387
who the boy feels close to.

21:38.475 --> 21:40.395
So you'd be cool
if Tucker got remarried

21:40.483 --> 21:41.957
and Tuck called
his new wife "Mom"?

21:42.053 --> 21:43.903
Now, why would you say
a vicious thing like that?

21:43.990 --> 21:46.738
I'm just saying, I just...
Can we please talk about me?

21:46.960 --> 21:49.324
How did you tell Tuck
that you were dating Ben?

21:49.412 --> 21:52.613
I... You know, on some level,
Tuck already knew.

21:52.717 --> 21:54.746
Look, all you have to do
is show up,

21:54.834 --> 21:57.988
make it clear what's happening,
answer her questions.

21:58.076 --> 22:00.012
All she wants to know is that
you're there for her,

22:00.099 --> 22:02.020
and you're not going anywhere
no matter what.

22:02.488 --> 22:03.510
[ Baby coos ]

22:03.598 --> 22:06.551
Okay, so, apparently Qadri
did do a pregnancy test,

22:06.639 --> 22:07.849
but she didn't
wait for the results

22:07.936 --> 22:09.513
because Avi was so sure
she knew what was going on.

22:09.600 --> 22:10.843
Okay, I'm gonna
say a thing,

22:10.931 --> 22:12.395
if only to spare you
the humiliation

22:12.483 --> 22:13.567
of your girlfriend
having to say it.

22:13.654 --> 22:16.161
- Trust, but verify.
- Trust, but verify!

22:16.915 --> 22:18.378
I heard about
this morning, too.

22:18.466 --> 22:19.975
You're really batting
a thousand today.

22:20.062 --> 22:21.310
Oh, it...
[ Sighs ]

22:21.398 --> 22:23.220
It was in the middle of the night!
[ Chuckles ]

22:23.307 --> 22:24.727
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

22:26.005 --> 22:27.513
Let's go back
to Germany,

22:27.686 --> 22:29.263
and just...

22:29.502 --> 22:31.958
- to when you saidthe thing to Teddy.
- Mm-hmm.

22:32.046 --> 22:33.357
Just focus on
what you were

22:33.445 --> 22:34.803
- feeling in that moment.
- Okay.

22:34.891 --> 22:36.884
Just be there,
and hold your arm strong.

22:37.006 --> 22:38.818
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

22:42.069 --> 22:43.880
And...

22:45.505 --> 22:46.927
Okay, there it is.

22:47.015 --> 22:48.849
- So, now, just let that go.
- Mm-hmm.

22:48.937 --> 22:50.708
Think about something else,
anything else,

22:50.883 --> 22:55.247
and let's check
the concept of nervousness.

22:55.727 --> 22:57.380
Of despair.

22:58.001 --> 22:59.794
Feeling of distrust.

22:59.897 --> 23:01.427
Feeling of distrust.

23:01.515 --> 23:03.833
Sensitivity to
someone else's distrust.

23:04.004 --> 23:05.327
Your distrust.

23:05.560 --> 23:07.872
Okay, so, it's yours.

23:08.044 --> 23:09.614
That's crazy.

23:09.763 --> 23:11.779
Do you feel
distrustful of Teddy?

23:12.005 --> 23:13.070
No.

23:13.158 --> 23:14.607
Can you remember
a time in your life

23:14.695 --> 23:15.989
when you felt that way?

23:17.046 --> 23:18.724
Uh...

23:19.060 --> 23:20.614
You know what?
That's a broad question.

23:20.702 --> 23:22.497
Let's just check
when it could've happened.

23:22.663 --> 23:23.946
Conception to five.

23:24.096 --> 23:25.608
Listen, w-why don't we just
skip to the Iraq War,

23:25.695 --> 23:27.373
'cause if we're talking about
trauma, that's where it started.

23:27.460 --> 23:28.693
So...
Okay.

23:28.781 --> 23:31.114
[ Sighs ] Was it
during the Iraq War?

23:31.231 --> 23:32.854
No, it's not
the war, then.

23:32.942 --> 23:34.739
Five to ten?

23:36.035 --> 23:37.948
Five?
Six?

23:38.168 --> 23:40.450
Seven?
Eight?

23:40.812 --> 23:43.614
Nine?
Ten?

23:44.372 --> 23:47.763
Do you have a memory of feeling
distrustful when you were ten?

23:47.851 --> 23:49.021
No.

23:51.186 --> 23:52.349
I don't know.

23:52.437 --> 23:53.638
Okay.

23:54.343 --> 23:57.247
Do you remember feeling joy at ten?
Probably. I was ten.

23:57.601 --> 23:59.630
[ Breathing deeply ]
Don't look too hard.

24:02.036 --> 24:03.490
There's probably a memory
sitting right there.

24:03.577 --> 24:05.693
Just the first thing
you think of.

24:08.008 --> 24:09.598
I won an award.

24:12.015 --> 24:14.364
There was
a Science Bee at school.

24:14.669 --> 24:17.068
And, um,
lasted three days.

24:17.156 --> 24:18.359
All grades.

24:18.447 --> 24:20.693
I beat everyone
at the school.

24:21.388 --> 24:22.560
How'd you feel
about that?

24:22.648 --> 24:24.724
Great. Proud.

24:25.407 --> 24:27.200
[ Inhales sharply ]

24:27.412 --> 24:29.232
Best that I've ever felt.

24:30.217 --> 24:31.661
It doesn't
sound like it.

24:37.991 --> 24:39.958
So you told him
to go to Germany.

24:40.071 --> 24:41.944
Because every time
I looked at him,

24:42.032 --> 24:43.365
I could see him
thinking about her.

24:43.452 --> 24:45.427
And he went,
and she rejected him.

24:45.515 --> 24:47.708
He went to Germany,
declared his love,

24:47.796 --> 24:49.568
and she declared it back.

24:49.656 --> 24:51.654
She loves him, Tom.
She always has.

24:51.742 --> 24:52.724
And... And now
there's a baby.

24:52.812 --> 24:53.646
I was kind of hoping
she was

24:53.734 --> 24:55.513
a one-night-stand-
between-friends baby.

24:55.601 --> 24:58.184
Nope, she is definitely
a love baby.

24:58.320 --> 24:59.405
Except for
the salty brunette

24:59.492 --> 25:01.239
who keeps showing up
back in his bed.

25:01.576 --> 25:03.779
Tom, I'm telling you this
as a friend...

25:03.867 --> 25:05.818
Owen and Teddy
are inevitable.

25:06.266 --> 25:07.429
Hey!

25:07.517 --> 25:08.606
Stem cells are here.

25:08.694 --> 25:09.958
OR 2 is prepped.

25:10.046 --> 25:11.191
My man!

25:11.279 --> 25:12.255
- See you in there.
- [ Chuckles ]

25:12.343 --> 25:13.833
Yeah. Ah. Mm!

25:13.937 --> 25:14.896
- Shut up.
- Shepherd.

25:14.984 --> 25:15.771
[ Glove snaps ]

25:15.859 --> 25:17.483
We're about to perform
an experimental procedure

25:17.570 --> 25:19.115
in which we might give
a paralyzed woman

25:19.202 --> 25:20.443
the use of her arms.

25:20.531 --> 25:23.505
"Inevitable"
doesn't scare me.

25:23.709 --> 25:25.005
[ Sighs ]

25:27.849 --> 25:29.895
- [ Monitor beeping ]
- Maggie: Let's go off bypass.

25:30.240 --> 25:32.023
Nico:
I-I was careful. I...

25:32.111 --> 25:33.856
I don't know if you used
the wrong amount of pressure

25:33.943 --> 25:35.316
or if the cement
was too liquid,

25:35.404 --> 25:37.174
but the pulmonary artery
is destroyed.

25:37.262 --> 25:39.199
I pieced it together, but
the graft is barely holding.

25:39.286 --> 25:40.360
What can I do?

25:40.448 --> 25:42.213
This is a temporary fix
at best.

25:42.301 --> 25:43.400
We could consider
putting him

25:43.487 --> 25:44.959
- on the transplant list.
- Transplant?

25:45.046 --> 25:48.024
If you can think of a better way
to save your patient from dying,

25:48.112 --> 25:49.146
I'd love to hear it.

25:49.234 --> 25:50.693
- [ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
- Damn it. Schmitt, suction!

25:50.780 --> 25:51.677
The repair
didn't hold?

25:51.765 --> 25:53.372
There is nothing here
to hold onto.

25:53.460 --> 25:55.442
Clamp!
[ Liquid suctioning ]

25:55.750 --> 25:56.919
Flap!

25:58.187 --> 25:59.284
Suction!

25:59.372 --> 26:01.411
[ Sighs ]

26:01.906 --> 26:03.599
I ran home after school.

26:04.552 --> 26:07.521
I had this big certificate
with a seal.

26:07.609 --> 26:11.312
You know, like, uh, foil.
[ Chuckles ]

26:11.400 --> 26:13.013
I remember that.

26:14.007 --> 26:17.567
And, uh, my mom was
waiting for me in the kitchen.

26:18.748 --> 26:20.177
And I was about
to show her it,

26:20.265 --> 26:22.622
and then she said,
"Owen, sit down."

26:23.114 --> 26:25.027
So I sat down,

26:26.622 --> 26:29.081
and... she told me
that my dad died...

26:30.289 --> 26:31.869
that day.

26:33.993 --> 26:36.058
So...
I'm sorry.

26:36.774 --> 26:40.003
What about the prize?
The certificate.

26:40.153 --> 26:41.245
What?

26:41.333 --> 26:43.487
Oh. I-I didn't tell her
about that.

26:43.575 --> 26:45.120
I didn't tell anybody.

26:45.312 --> 26:47.128
I was, um,
you know...

26:47.577 --> 26:51.089
I was ashamed
that I was so proud,

26:51.684 --> 26:57.058
that I was so... happy
when she was so sad.

26:59.833 --> 27:01.816
And my dad was, um...

27:02.001 --> 27:04.679
Owen, I think you've been
reliving this moment ever since.

27:04.767 --> 27:06.649
No, no, no.

27:06.737 --> 27:08.907
I think you don't
trust joy.

27:09.375 --> 27:12.696
I think you stop it before
something terrible happens,

27:12.997 --> 27:16.063
before the bad news comes.
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:16.432 --> 27:18.102
But it's not
coming anymore.

27:18.373 --> 27:20.196
That moment is over.

27:20.810 --> 27:23.524
It came,
and you're okay.

27:24.312 --> 27:26.352
So let's
stop the replay.

27:30.852 --> 27:32.515
How?

27:32.821 --> 27:34.610
Okay,
I want you to...

27:35.318 --> 27:39.043
I want you to put your hand on
your wrist like this, okay?

27:39.178 --> 27:41.704
And then put your hand
on your forehead.

27:41.857 --> 27:44.250
[♪♪]

27:44.734 --> 27:47.735
And just sit
and breathe.

27:48.460 --> 27:50.623
[ Breathes deeply ]

27:50.897 --> 27:54.438
[♪♪]

27:54.821 --> 27:56.602
[ Sobbing ]

27:57.607 --> 28:02.672
[♪♪]

28:03.679 --> 28:08.454
[♪♪]

28:14.474 --> 28:17.958
Woman on P.A.: <i>Dr. Franco,
please call extension 523.</i>

28:18.046 --> 28:20.927
<i>Dr. Franco,
please call extension 523.</i>

28:21.143 --> 28:22.802
You don't quit, huh?

28:22.897 --> 28:24.255
You bring
a "Big Book"?

28:24.343 --> 28:26.176
You planning
to read to me

28:26.295 --> 28:28.232
while I'm too weak
to stop you?

28:28.388 --> 28:29.739
I just wanted
to update you.

28:29.827 --> 28:32.614
Dr. Pierce had an emergency
with another patient.

28:32.755 --> 28:35.498
So... she didn't
do your surgery.

28:36.146 --> 28:37.628
I did.

28:38.591 --> 28:39.593
Oh.

28:39.681 --> 28:40.714
[ Chuckles ]

28:40.802 --> 28:42.325
So I can sue you.

28:42.662 --> 28:44.177
Buy me
a new pair of shoes.

28:44.265 --> 28:45.598
You do
whatever you want to.

28:45.686 --> 28:47.919
Although it would make you
a serious ingrate,

28:48.007 --> 28:49.919
seeing how I saved
your damn life,

28:50.083 --> 28:51.560
you stubborn drunk!

28:51.694 --> 28:53.114
[ Scoffs ]

28:53.819 --> 28:55.403
[ Laughs ]

28:58.378 --> 28:59.724
[ Scoffs ]

29:00.325 --> 29:03.879
[ Chuckles ] Ow, ow. Hurts.

29:04.082 --> 29:05.661
Hurts when I laugh.

29:05.749 --> 29:06.824
Well, it ought to hurt.

29:06.912 --> 29:08.783
You punctured
your heart with a shoe.

29:08.871 --> 29:09.878
Heh.

29:09.965 --> 29:11.707
That's a new bottom
if I ever heard one.

29:11.795 --> 29:13.184
[ Breathing deeply ]

29:13.972 --> 29:16.137
I had 17 years.

29:16.418 --> 29:17.864
I know.

29:19.635 --> 29:21.176
I want 'em back.

29:21.505 --> 29:23.375
[ Monitor beeping ]

29:25.545 --> 29:28.168
The years
don't matter, Gemma.

29:28.255 --> 29:29.903
Just today.

29:30.543 --> 29:34.879
It's just... It's just
one day at a time.

29:34.967 --> 29:38.460
You start your count all
over again and tell me that.

29:39.371 --> 29:41.878
Well, not long ago,
I almost did.

29:42.215 --> 29:44.286
I slid my chip
across a bar,

29:44.441 --> 29:46.786
traded it
for a line of shots.

29:47.245 --> 29:48.778
You did what?

29:49.520 --> 29:51.254
It was a very bad day.

29:51.795 --> 29:53.278
Tell me more.

29:54.169 --> 29:56.145
You stubborn drunk.

29:56.965 --> 29:59.465
[ Chuckles ]

30:01.707 --> 30:04.077
[ Inhales sharply ]

30:07.635 --> 30:08.748
[ Respirator hissing ]

30:08.835 --> 30:10.715
Amelia: Thank you
for finding this study.

30:10.803 --> 30:13.364
Thank you for inspiring me
to find this study.

30:13.452 --> 30:14.573
I'll thank you both
to stop

30:14.661 --> 30:16.371
before I vomit
into an open spine.

30:16.459 --> 30:18.162
Okay,
suspend her breathing.

30:18.653 --> 30:19.817
[ Machine beeps ]

30:20.045 --> 30:21.548
Okay.

30:21.801 --> 30:23.668
[♪♪]

30:24.309 --> 30:26.371
[ Monitor beeping ]

30:26.634 --> 30:29.247
Bailey: I know you love Ben
and I know you didn't mean to,

30:29.335 --> 30:30.918
but it hurt
your father's feelings,

30:31.005 --> 30:33.168
so you just have to
say you're sorry

30:33.255 --> 30:35.248
and go back to
calling Ben "Ben."

30:35.335 --> 30:36.369
Wait, hold on.

30:36.457 --> 30:37.879
Pop-Pop.

30:38.098 --> 30:40.481
[♪♪]

30:40.643 --> 30:42.746
Hey, what happened?
Something went wrong.

30:42.834 --> 30:44.083
- They took him. Dr. Bailey,
- What? Josh should be out by...

30:44.170 --> 30:45.833
something went
really wrong.

30:45.965 --> 30:48.776
Okay, uh,
I'll find out, okay?

30:48.864 --> 30:50.548
I'll be right back.

30:50.871 --> 30:52.450
[♪♪]

30:52.629 --> 30:54.887
[ Flatline ]

30:57.465 --> 30:58.628
No.

30:58.715 --> 31:00.059
[ Flatline stops ]

31:00.176 --> 31:01.934
How?

31:02.127 --> 31:04.543
Massive pulmonary artery
embolism.

31:04.715 --> 31:05.668
The bone cement...

31:05.755 --> 31:06.958
Okay, wait, I don't want
to hear it from you.

31:07.045 --> 31:08.661
I want to hear it
from you.

31:10.535 --> 31:12.293
The cement leaked,
causing a blood clot.

31:12.381 --> 31:13.963
He went
into cardiac arrest.

31:14.051 --> 31:16.628
Dr. Pierce tried to repair
the pulmonary artery.

31:16.715 --> 31:17.933
We tried everything
we could, and we...

31:18.020 --> 31:18.955
You made a mistake

31:19.043 --> 31:20.838
on a healthy
21-year-old man.

31:20.925 --> 31:23.223
And that man is now dead.
That's what happened.

31:23.356 --> 31:28.161
[♪♪]

31:28.590 --> 31:31.621
[ Door slides open, closes ]

31:31.874 --> 31:32.957
[♪♪]

31:33.347 --> 31:34.970
Schmitt, you close.

31:35.058 --> 31:36.167
And you...

31:36.255 --> 31:38.048
You are gonna stand
right next to me

31:38.135 --> 31:40.723
and take in every moment
of that grandfather's grief.

31:40.811 --> 31:44.247
And if you're a good surgeon,
you'll remember it.

31:44.335 --> 31:46.338
And you'll never make
this mistake again.

31:46.676 --> 31:52.176
[♪♪]

31:52.959 --> 31:58.606
[♪♪]

32:00.519 --> 32:02.254
[ Clears throat ]

32:04.505 --> 32:07.588
Look, the way I see it is we can
keep working in awkward silence

32:07.675 --> 32:09.965
until it's time for you to
go home, or... I vote that.

32:10.053 --> 32:12.716
...or you can tell me what
you meant by "I was right."

32:12.855 --> 32:15.377
'Cause I could, maybe,
help you feel,

32:15.465 --> 32:17.048
I don't know,
one drop less crappy.

32:17.135 --> 32:18.934
You told me
not to go looking,

32:19.022 --> 32:20.315
[sighs]
and you were right.

32:20.403 --> 32:21.699
- That's all, so...
- Jo, I told you not to go

32:21.786 --> 32:23.192
looking
if everything was okay.

32:23.380 --> 32:25.768
You went looking, so maybe
everything was not okay.

32:25.856 --> 32:26.950
Maybe you needed that.

32:27.038 --> 32:28.723
No, no. You know what?
I had everything.

32:28.811 --> 32:31.817
I had a marriage
and a job and...

32:31.964 --> 32:34.129
Yeah,
Alex is right here.

32:34.374 --> 32:36.674
You got a great job
right here.

32:36.762 --> 32:37.752
[ Chuckling ]
You're doing it right now.

32:37.840 --> 32:39.496
I'm spraying water
on a paper towel,

32:39.584 --> 32:42.117
and Alex
is anything but happy.

32:42.295 --> 32:44.221
'Cause he's
worried about you.

32:44.309 --> 32:45.748
He's trying to help.
Come on.

32:46.051 --> 32:47.708
I knew it.
I knew it.

32:47.795 --> 32:50.168
He sent you here.
No, he didn't.

32:50.293 --> 32:51.661
Jo, that's not
what this is.

32:51.749 --> 32:52.674
Then what is it?

32:52.762 --> 32:54.268
The guy's worried,
okay?

32:54.356 --> 32:55.715
He's...
wondering.

32:55.803 --> 32:57.269
Why don't you just
communicate with him?

32:57.356 --> 32:58.974
'Cause it would only hurt,
and it won't help.

32:59.061 --> 33:00.061
[ Sighs ]

33:02.506 --> 33:03.539
You don't know that.

33:03.627 --> 33:04.737
I had all this happy,

33:04.825 --> 33:06.837
and I just...
tossed it aside

33:06.925 --> 33:07.985
like it
would always exist.

33:08.073 --> 33:09.924
I mean, we...
We see it all the time.

33:10.190 --> 33:12.878
We diagnose patients
with terrible diseases

33:12.965 --> 33:14.945
or we tell someone that
their husband dropped dead

33:15.033 --> 33:16.213
of...
Of a heart attack,

33:16.301 --> 33:18.196
and all they can say is
they were fine yesterday,

33:18.283 --> 33:19.955
and they were.
They were fine.

33:20.175 --> 33:21.604
I was fine.

33:22.518 --> 33:23.846
And I took it
for granted,

33:23.934 --> 33:27.002
and now it feels impossible
to get it back.

33:27.261 --> 33:28.643
[ Syringe clatters ]

33:30.791 --> 33:32.510
It was Mer.

33:33.700 --> 33:36.113
It was Meredith that asked me
to look in on you.

33:36.307 --> 33:39.744
She knows how our parents
can screw with our heads.

33:40.190 --> 33:41.875
I'm here, okay?

33:41.963 --> 33:42.708
I'm working.

33:42.795 --> 33:44.721
You came to work
drunk, Jo.

33:46.215 --> 33:47.838
You're still drunk.

33:49.045 --> 33:50.125
I can smell it.

33:50.213 --> 33:52.041
I'm thinking vodka
in the water bottle.

33:52.425 --> 33:54.704
I'm glad you had the decency
not to see any patients today.

33:54.791 --> 33:55.633
- That's nice.
- You don't know

33:55.721 --> 33:57.893
- what you're talking about.
- You're in a lot of pain,

33:58.045 --> 33:59.188
and you're trying
to numb it.

33:59.276 --> 34:00.846
I get that, okay?

34:01.001 --> 34:01.941
It's not gonna work.

34:02.029 --> 34:04.110
I'm telling you.
You're gonna ruin your life.

34:04.198 --> 34:05.830
Jo, don't leave.

34:06.295 --> 34:07.969
Just talk to me
for a second.

34:08.056 --> 34:09.208
I'm trying to help you.

34:09.533 --> 34:15.510
[♪♪]

34:16.083 --> 34:18.643
You set foot in this hospital
drunk again,

34:19.831 --> 34:22.114
you're not gonna be met
with compassion.

34:22.588 --> 34:28.705
[♪♪]

34:30.056 --> 34:31.612
[ Door slams ]

34:39.518 --> 34:41.181
<i>Kadiatou's "Say Something"
plays...</i>

34:41.465 --> 34:45.784
[♪♪]

34:46.313 --> 34:47.226
[ Door slides open ]

34:47.315 --> 34:48.288
[ Monitor beeping ]

34:48.375 --> 34:53.353
<i>♪ Say something,
I'm giving up on you ♪</i>

34:53.525 --> 34:54.978
The surgery went well.

34:55.067 --> 34:56.310
I see that.

34:56.405 --> 34:57.637
Yours?

34:58.683 --> 35:00.683
- <i>♪ I'll be the one ♪</i>
- Did not.

35:01.005 --> 35:03.621
- I'm sorry.
- <i>♪ If you want me to ♪</i>

35:03.709 --> 35:04.755
Bailey: [ Voice breaking ]
And Dr. Pierce

35:04.842 --> 35:07.316
did everything she could,
but...

35:07.505 --> 35:09.498
[ Sobbing ] ...the
damage was too extensive.

35:09.585 --> 35:11.504
I'm...

35:11.592 --> 35:14.005
You said we'd be lucky
to have that doctor.

35:14.093 --> 35:17.426
You said Josh would be in good hands.
[ Breathes deeply ]

35:18.295 --> 35:21.019
- [ Crying ] What happened?
- I know. I know.

35:21.418 --> 35:23.183
[ Sobbing continues ]
Oh.

35:23.683 --> 35:26.410
I'm so sorry.

35:26.683 --> 35:28.288
[ Sniffles, crying ]

35:28.375 --> 35:29.378
<i>♪ And I... ♪</i>

35:29.465 --> 35:30.988
My boy.

35:31.835 --> 35:34.708
<i>♪ ...am feeling so small ♪</i>

35:34.795 --> 35:36.293
[♪♪]

35:36.381 --> 35:37.664
[ Breathes deeply,
crying ]

35:37.835 --> 35:40.458
<i>♪ It was over my head ♪</i>

35:40.545 --> 35:41.918
[ Baby cooing ]

35:42.005 --> 35:43.838
<i>♪ And I knew nothing at all ♪</i>

35:43.926 --> 35:45.379
Hey.

35:45.755 --> 35:47.875
Yeah,
it's nice to meet you.

35:50.137 --> 35:55.558
<i>♪ Say something,
I'm giving up on you ♪</i>

35:55.646 --> 35:56.646
Hey.

35:57.086 --> 35:59.152
[ Cooing continues ]

36:00.180 --> 36:02.788
<i>♪ And I'm sorry that I couldn't ♪</i>

36:02.876 --> 36:05.458
- <i>♪ Get to you ♪</i>
- Okay, now all we do is wait.

36:05.680 --> 36:08.001
I hope we didn't
get their hopes up for nothing.

36:08.136 --> 36:10.469
Oh. Thank you.

36:10.613 --> 36:11.914
How do you feel about.

36:12.002 --> 36:14.985
- ♪ I would've followed you ♪
- sushi burritos?

36:15.214 --> 36:18.173
That sounds like
a culinary abomination,

36:18.312 --> 36:20.540
and I need one
immediately.

36:21.381 --> 36:22.844
Could you give me
one minute, though?

36:22.932 --> 36:24.969
<i>♪ I'm giving up on you ♪</i>

36:25.057 --> 36:26.057
[ Clears throat ]

36:26.247 --> 36:28.391
[ Inhales sharply ]

36:28.964 --> 36:30.837
Look, I know you think
you're being brave

36:30.925 --> 36:32.641
by fighting for Teddy,

36:33.050 --> 36:34.543
but that's not
what's happening here.

36:34.631 --> 36:37.022
Y-Your hopes are up.
They're way up...

36:37.110 --> 36:38.338
And hope scares you.

36:38.425 --> 36:39.376
And that's why
you're, uh,

36:39.464 --> 36:42.477
hiding behind a very pretty,
very decent guy

36:42.618 --> 36:45.266
to cover the fact that you're
still hung up on Owen Hunt.

36:45.434 --> 36:48.057
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

36:48.215 --> 36:49.838
A thing I've learned

36:50.149 --> 36:52.688
is that life
is a series of choices.

36:52.994 --> 36:56.579
And that sometimes,
there is an easier, softer way.

36:57.414 --> 37:00.977
- H-He is uncomplicated, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

37:01.996 --> 37:03.415
And it so refreshing.

37:03.503 --> 37:06.538
Oh. It is like diving into
a cold pool on a hot day.

37:06.626 --> 37:07.626
Ah.

37:07.735 --> 37:09.563
Am I hung up on Owen?

37:10.370 --> 37:11.516
Sure.

37:11.835 --> 37:13.891
Maybe I always will be.

37:14.782 --> 37:16.587
But am I using Link?

37:16.873 --> 37:18.040
No.

37:18.638 --> 37:21.001
I'm just choosing
an easier path.

37:22.423 --> 37:23.915
You might want
to try it.

37:24.043 --> 37:27.759
<i>♪ Say something,
I'm giving up on you ♪</i>

37:28.005 --> 37:31.790
[♪♪]

37:31.970 --> 37:33.048
[ Sighs ]

37:33.136 --> 37:35.813
<i>♪ Say something ♪</i>

37:36.620 --> 37:39.953
[ Keyboard clacking ]

37:40.135 --> 37:41.640
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

37:41.727 --> 37:43.110
Levi: Hey.

37:43.198 --> 37:45.653
I was looking all over
for you.

37:46.032 --> 37:48.165
Thought you might've
tried to postpone.

37:48.300 --> 37:50.579
Can't just postpone
a job interview.

37:51.045 --> 37:52.509
Yeah, I know.

37:52.950 --> 37:55.323
But they could make
an exception, you know?

37:55.695 --> 37:57.259
Because of
what happened today.

37:57.392 --> 38:00.147
Oh, you mean 'cause I
screwed up so completely

38:00.235 --> 38:01.462
that someone's dead?

38:01.550 --> 38:04.555
Oh, yeah, sure, let me just
call up the hiring committee

38:04.657 --> 38:06.173
and fill them in, Levi.

38:06.974 --> 38:08.539
So, you think
you're in the best condition

38:08.626 --> 38:09.985
to interview
for your dream job?

38:10.096 --> 38:12.118
Just e-mail 'em, okay?

38:12.891 --> 38:14.342
Then we can
get out of here.

38:14.465 --> 38:15.918
No, you don't get it!

38:16.005 --> 38:18.263
'Cause you let failure
hold you back your whole life.

38:18.526 --> 38:20.842
It's basically
your entire identity.

38:22.005 --> 38:23.435
But it's not mine.

38:23.640 --> 38:25.973
[ Skype tone ringing ]

38:26.440 --> 38:28.127
<i>So much of the world operates</i>

38:28.215 --> 38:30.263
<i>without us
ever thinking about it.</i>

38:31.527 --> 38:33.020
Dr. Kim,
it's nice to see you.

38:33.108 --> 38:35.061
Your application
is tremendously impressive.

38:35.202 --> 38:36.638
Hey, Dr. Hogans,

38:36.726 --> 38:38.685
thank you for making the time
to talk to me.

38:38.773 --> 38:41.686
I've wanted to be a part of your
program since I... [ Door slams ]

38:41.774 --> 38:45.107
...since I first, uh,
chose ortho as my specialty.

38:45.638 --> 38:48.412
Meredith: <i>We expect it
to work out in our favor,</i>

38:49.201 --> 38:51.224
<i>and, most of the time, it does.</i>

38:54.046 --> 38:55.596
[ Sighs ]

39:09.717 --> 39:12.248
Let's just go home,
order in.

39:12.336 --> 39:15.521
I have to go to my place
and get some clean clothes.

39:15.779 --> 39:18.239
I'm so tired,
I might just crash there.

39:18.335 --> 39:19.678
Move in with me.

39:21.835 --> 39:23.178
What?

39:23.295 --> 39:25.123
I love you, Maggie.

39:25.211 --> 39:28.240
I don't want
to take it for granted.

39:29.052 --> 39:30.721
I don't want to miss it.

39:32.498 --> 39:33.627
Yeah.

39:33.779 --> 39:35.224
Move in with me.

39:35.585 --> 39:37.732
[♪♪]

39:38.035 --> 39:41.698
We worry about the future
and think about the past.

39:42.310 --> 39:44.607
[ Owen snoring ]

39:45.061 --> 39:48.264
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh...

39:48.375 --> 39:49.209
[ Grunts ]

39:49.296 --> 39:50.548
Okay.

39:50.635 --> 39:51.615
Hey, come here.

39:51.711 --> 39:52.880
Come here, come here,
come here.

39:52.967 --> 39:54.342
Hey.

39:54.804 --> 39:56.709
[ Cellphone keyboard clacking ]

39:56.877 --> 39:59.500
- <i>♪ Somewhere past tomorrow ♪</i>
[ Cellphone blooping ]

39:59.728 --> 40:01.787
- <i>♪ Is better than it seems ♪</i>
- Teddy. Look.

40:01.875 --> 40:05.109
- [ Scoffs ] - [ Leo babbles ]
<i>♪ Would like to ever dream ♪</i>

40:07.583 --> 40:10.304
- Okay. [ Sighs ]
- <i>♪ If you're ever broken... ♪</i>

40:10.392 --> 40:13.740
<i>And we so often miss
what's right in front of us.</i>

40:14.022 --> 40:16.944
Woman on TV: <i>It's a tiny field outside Lake...</i>
<i>♪ Being told to show ♪</i>

40:17.085 --> 40:19.014
Alex:
You were drinking at work?

40:19.412 --> 40:21.705
<i>♪ Tired... ♪</i>

40:21.908 --> 40:24.288
Jo, I'm done.
The field...

40:24.375 --> 40:25.627
You hear me?
I'm done.

40:25.715 --> 40:27.912
I need you to hear me.
I need you to talk to me.

40:28.139 --> 40:30.925
- <i>♪ Know you're bound for glory ♪</i>
- I love you, Jo. I love you, but I...

40:31.012 --> 40:32.787
If you love me,
you will let me...

40:32.875 --> 40:34.868
No, no, no, no, we're not
playing that game anymore.

40:35.085 --> 40:37.525
We're not playing that "if you
love me, you'd leave me alone."

40:37.684 --> 40:39.768
You went to Pittsburgh,
and we were good.

40:39.855 --> 40:40.939
- Stop.
- We were good,

40:41.027 --> 40:41.788
and then you come back,

40:41.875 --> 40:43.790
and you won't talk to me,
and you're drinking at work.

40:43.877 --> 40:44.508
Please.

40:44.596 --> 40:45.847
So how about
I just go to Pittsburgh

40:45.934 --> 40:47.767
and find out what the hell
happened to my wife?!

40:47.854 --> 40:49.928
<i>♪ So get up off your knees ♪</i>

40:50.016 --> 40:50.847
Huh?!

40:50.935 --> 40:52.764
- <i>♪ Hope is still alive ♪</i>
- <i>We take what's good and easy</i>

40:52.852 --> 40:54.841
<i>and working for granted...</i>

40:56.186 --> 40:57.917
<i>♪ I know you'll find ♪</i>

40:58.005 --> 41:01.208
I will talk to you
when I'm ready to talk to you.

41:01.365 --> 41:04.338
And if you ever threaten
to go to Pittsburgh again,

41:04.425 --> 41:05.936
I will leave you.

41:07.365 --> 41:08.887
Are we clear?

41:10.770 --> 41:12.856
If you ever
come to work drunk again,

41:13.045 --> 41:14.628
I'll tell Bailey.

41:17.175 --> 41:18.262
Great.

41:18.350 --> 41:19.801
We have a deal.

41:20.114 --> 41:23.372
<i>...until it's no longer good
and easy and working for us.</i>

41:24.035 --> 41:27.770
<i>It's normal,
but we can do better</i>

41:28.049 --> 41:30.247
because there are tiny,
beautiful gifts

41:30.335 --> 41:31.521
we're given every day.

41:31.609 --> 41:33.045
Here we go.

41:34.222 --> 41:37.156
So, the reason why

41:38.046 --> 41:40.757
you saw Dr. DeLuca here
the other night

41:40.845 --> 41:44.132
was because he and I have been
spending more time together.

41:44.234 --> 41:45.450
Is he
your boyfriend?

41:45.546 --> 41:46.552
He is.

41:46.640 --> 41:48.048
What's that mean?

41:48.135 --> 41:51.640
Well, that means
that I like him a lot.

41:51.874 --> 41:53.917
Not more than you,
but a lot.

41:54.005 --> 41:55.628
Are you gonna
kiss him?

41:55.715 --> 41:56.755
Probably.

41:56.843 --> 41:58.914
- Ew, gross!
- Oh, gross!

41:59.002 --> 42:00.996
- Is he gonna sleep on the couch again?
- [ Giggles ]

42:01.083 --> 42:03.496
No, he won't be
sleeping on the couch,

42:03.584 --> 42:05.882
but he may be coming around
a lot more, so...

42:06.348 --> 42:08.046
But I'm not
going anywhere.

42:08.373 --> 42:09.498
You're stuck with me.

42:09.586 --> 42:11.048
Can he leave
his guitar at home?

42:11.136 --> 42:12.513
[ Laughter ]

42:12.601 --> 42:15.746
And it's up to us to appreciate
them to the fullest

42:16.138 --> 42:17.391
while we can.

42:17.844 --> 42:20.502
[♪♪]
